    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-03T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-03T08:00:00-05:00" n="280"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control Austria/7–345: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 280<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-03T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 3, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2850. Our 2842, July 2.<note n="1" xml:id="d280fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>June 30 [A]FHQ directed Brit Eight Army to contact local Russ Commander Sov
                    Forces in Styria to arrange for Sov withdrawal and subsequent Brit movement into
                    Styria and Carinthia areas of Austria.</p>
                <p>July 1 Brit officer commanding Fifth Corps met Russians at Sov Fourth Army <gloss
                        target="#t_HQs1">HQ</gloss> delivered letter from <gloss target="#t_CG1"
                        >CG</gloss> Eight Army addressed to <persName corresp="#p_TMFI1"
                        >Tolbukhin</persName> and discussed withdrawal Russ forces from Styria. Russ
                    Commander said he had not reed any orders to withdraw and until such time he
                    would maintain his position. USS[R] Com also asked what Brit intended to do with
                    White Russ Corps now in Brit occupied zone to which Brit officer replied he had
                    no knowledge of its existence. July 2 Brit officer <gloss target="#t_CG1"
                        >CG</gloss> Five Corps again met Russ and reed written reply addressed to
                        <gloss target="#t_CG1">CG</gloss> Eight Army saying latter’s letter would be
                    delivered promptly to Sov <gloss target="#t_CinC1">CinC</gloss> Central Army
                    group Marshal <persName corresp="#p_K1">Koniev</persName>; that until receipt
                    orders from <gloss target="#t_CinC1">CinC</gloss> Russ Forces in Styria could
                    not be withdrawn. Note was cordial in tone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
